reviews.review_text: Sounds Incredible, Awesome Energy Folks, IMO this is one of the better FOB/AUDs I've heard in months.  The sound is rich and full, not tinny and distant.  The band's energy is all there too, no holding back on this one!  Grab this amazing Rolfe/Miller AUD!
Hard to believe this is an aud This show is a frigging miracle.
Sound Wow this 1979 on of best Aud from any year 5 stars well worth the 3 cd's. 79 is a very underated year and this show proves it one the best sounding Aud's you will find anywhere

Also........ Plus, please note: The second set - beginning with Scarlet Begonias - is about two hours long, with only one stop between Long Distance Runner and Estimated Prophet. One monstrous, epic jam. Unforgettable show.
Nice recording I'm a suckah for good AUD recordings. Great sound and above-average performance. Well done, Steve Rolfe.
Best source to date 1/15 Hate to say it, but this beats the board.  Much fuller sound and a lot more like being there.  Love it.  Awesome pull.

My Sister Was There.... ...for the earlier November show that was cancelled.  She recounts thousands of heads hitting the streets of New Haven as their trips were just taking off, what a scene indeed!

This make up show is very nice, 1979 getting off to a great start.  I’ll take a sweet AUD like this any day over a cold and steely SB....

Good show, GREAT recording... & some pics~ I gave this one a spin on its 42nd anniversary, and found the song selection sweet & the recording itself excellent!  God bless the early tapers, who had the foresight to record as many shows as they did so that we could enjoy them oh-so-many years later!
I also searched the net looking for pics of the New Haven Coliseum while listening, and found several pics of the actual show itself, including several shots from both outside & inside the venue.  There are nice pics in all~
